# JetBrains IDE
.idea/

# R2 cutover (2026-07-21): media is served from the blackdays-media R2
# bucket via MEDIA_BASE, not from disk. Kept at top-level /media/ (rather
# than public/media/) because `astro build` copies the entire public/ dir
# into dist/ unconditionally, ignoring .gitignore — leaving it under public/
# would still balloon every build/deploy with 667MB of already-uploaded
# media. Files stay on disk here as a local working copy; not committed.
/media/
